## Dependent Options

Control what happens to associated records when parent is destroyed.

```ruby
class User < ApplicationRecord
  # :destroy - Delete associated records and run callbacks
  has_many :articles, dependent: :destroy
  
  # :delete_all - Delete associated records without callbacks (faster)
  has_many :comments, dependent: :delete_all
  
  # :nullify - Set foreign key to NULL
  has_many :drafts, dependent: :nullify
  
  # :restrict_with_error - Prevent deletion, add error
  has_many :published_articles, dependent: :restrict_with_error
  
  # :restrict_with_exception - Prevent deletion, raise exception
  has_many :orders, dependent: :restrict_with_exception
  
  # No option - Do nothing (orphan records)
  has_many :views
end
```

**Choosing dependent option:**
- `:destroy` - When associated records should be deleted with callbacks
- `:delete_all` - When associated records should be deleted fast (no callbacks)
- `:nullify` - When associated records should remain but not be connected
- `:restrict_with_error` - When deletion should be prevented (soft)
- `:restrict_with_exception` - When deletion must be prevented (hard)

